Four persons have died in cult clashes in Delta and Anambra states. Three of them were killed on Tuesday morning in Owhase and Ovwian communities in Udu council area of Delta. Residents reportedly woke up to see the body of one of the dead simply identified as Otobo, close to New York Junction, along Udu Road. A photo of late Otobo obtained by this reporter showed he was stabbed multiple times in the face, arm and belly. Sources said all three incidents may be connected. In Anambra one person was killed and another seriously wounded in Okija, Ihiala council area. The Nation gathered yesterday that no fewer than seven persons have been killed in the community in similar circumstances since November 2020 The violence led to the removal of the former Divisional Police Officer on Monday, while his replacement took office yesterday. A senior police officer confirmed the incident.